        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Show session cleanup dry-run counts by label",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a text-mode `sessions cleanup --dry-run` breakdown by session label.\n- Show kept, removed, and total counts per label, with unlabeled sessions grouped as `(unlabeled)`.\n- Update CLI docs and the changelog for the new preview output.\n\n## Why\n\nThis addresses [#76826](https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/76826) by making dry-run cleanup impact easier to scan by label without changing cleanup policy or JSON output.\n\nCloses openclaw/openclaw#76826\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior or issue addressed: `openclaw sessions cleanup --dry-run` now shows a per-label summary with kept, removed, and total counts after the existing per-session action table.\n- Real environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on Windows, branch `feat/session-cleanup-label-breakdown`, running the actual CLI through `pnpm openclaw` against a temporary real `sessions.json` store under `%TEMP%`. The store had four real entries: two `Work`, one `Personal`, and one unlabeled; two entries pointed at existing transcript files and two pointed at missing transcript files.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```powershell\n$env:NO_COLOR = \"1\"\npnpm openclaw sessions cleanup --store C:\\Users\\<user>\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\openclaw-pr-79609-proof\\sessions.json --dry-run --fix-missing\n```\n\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output): Copied live terminal output from the actual local OpenClaw CLI run:\n\n```text\nSession store: C:\\Users\\<user>\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\openclaw-pr-79609-proof\\sessions.json\nMaintenance mode: enforce\nEntries: 4 -> 2 (remove 2)\nWould prune missing transcripts: 2\nWould retire stale direct DM sessions: 0\nWould prune stale: 0\nWould cap overflow: 0\nWould prune unreferenced artifacts: 0\n\nPlanned session actions:\nAction           Key                        Age       Model          Flags\nkeep             newWork                    just now  pi:opus        id:new-work\nkeep             unlabeled                  just now  pi:opus        id:unlabeled\nprune-missing    personal                   12h ago   pi:opus        id:personal\nprune-missing    oldWork                    24h ago   pi:opus        id:old-work\n\nSession cleanup by label:\nLabel                              Keep   Remove    Total\nPersonal                              0        1        1\nWork                                  1        1        2\n(unlabeled)                           1        0        1\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: The dry-run output retained the existing planned action table and added `Session cleanup by label:` with the expected counts: `Work` kept 1 / removed 1 / total 2, `Personal` kept 0 / removed 1 / total 1, and `(unlabeled)` kept 1 / removed 0 / total 1.\n- What was not tested: No known gaps for the text-mode CLI behavior covered by this proof. JSON output was intentionally left unchanged; the PR also includes targeted unit coverage for the text renderer.\n- Before evidence (optional but encouraged): Before this patch, the same text renderer only printed the per-session `Planned session actions:` table and had no `Session cleanup by label:` section.\n\n## Testing\n\n- `pnpm test src/commands/sessions-cleanup.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/commands/sessions-cleanup.ts src/commands/sessions-cleanup.test.ts docs/cli/sessions.md CHANGELOG.md`\n- `pnpm check:changed`",
